/*!
    \example sslserver
    \title Server Name Indication (SNI) Server Example
    \ingroup examples-network
    \brief Demonstrates how to respond to an SNI request over an encrypted (SSL) connection

    This example uses QSslSocket to demonstrate how to respond to an SNI request over an
    encrypted connection with the right certificate and key.

    \note Add the following lines to your hosts file for this example to work correctly:

    \code
    127.0.0.1  server.ssltestserver.org  server
    ::1        server.ssltestserver.org  server
    \endcode

    \image sslserver-example.png
